# Project Structure Guide

## Directory Structure
- `frontend/` - React application using Vite
- `backend/` - Node.js backend following DDD principles
- `prisma/` - Database schema and migrations

## Key Technologies
- Frontend: React + Vite + TailwindCSS + Shadcn/ui
- Backend: Node.js with DDD architecture
- Database: Prisma ORM
- API: RESTful endpoints

## Development Guidelines
1. All code and comments must be in English
2. Follow Domain-Driven Design patterns in the backend
3. Use TailwindCSS for styling
4. Implement responsive design for all components
5. Follow React best practices and hooks guidelines

## Port Configuration
- Frontend: Runs on port 3000-3003 (auto-selected)
- Backend: Default port will be specified in environment variables

## Important Files
- `PDR.md` - Product Requirements Document (English only)
- `task-list.md` - Project tasks and progress tracking
